# 11.13 Variation of specific work and compressor airflow with ambient temperature.
# Simulating the effects of ambient temperature on performance
# 11.14 Variation of power output and thermal efficiency with ambient temperature.

When gas turbines are designed to operate at lower compressor pressure ratios, the compressor inlet choking is less severe. This will result in a larger increase in power output during constant gas generator speed operation, due to the larger increase in maximum to minimum temperature ratios and airflow rate as the ambient temperature decreases, particularly if the design compressor pressure ratio is below the maximum cycle specific work condition. In this case the resultant increase in pressure ratio will also contribute to an increase in gas turbine power output.

Figure 11.12 shows that, at lower ambient temperatures below –12 degrees Celsius, the gas turbine performance is constrained by the compressor non-dimensional speed, N₁/√T₁. The operating point on the compressor characteristic will now correspond to the –30 degrees Celsius case, as shown in Fig. 11.9. The compressor will continue to operate at this point, restricting the increase in compressor ratio and thus the maximum to minimum cycle temperature ratio, as shown in Figure 11.10. Therefore, as the ambient temperature decreases below –15 Celsius, the decrease in specific work will be more acute, as shown in Fig. ",What does Figure 11.12 indicate about gas turbine performance at ambient temperatures below –12 degrees Celsius?,"Figure 11.12 indicates that gas turbine performance is constrained by the compressor non-dimensional speed, N₁/√T₁, at ambient temperatures below –12 degrees Celsius.","At ambient temperatures below –12 degrees Celsius, the performance of the gas turbine is limited by N₁/√T₁, as shown in Figure 11.12.","The constraint on gas turbine performance below –12 degrees Celsius is due to the compressor non-dimensional speed, according to Figure 11.12.","Figure 11.12 shows that below –12 degrees Celsius, the gas turbine's operation is restricted by the compressor's non-dimensional speed.","Gas turbine performance at ambient temperatures below –12 degrees Celsius is limited by N₁/√T₁, as depicted in Figure 11.12."
